EPIB 607	Inferential Statistics.	Introduction to the basic principles of statistical inference used in clinical and epidemiologic research. Topics include variability; methods of processing and describing data; sampling and sampling distributions; inferences regarding means and proportions, non-parametric methods, regression and correlation.	0.0	Epidemiology and Biostatistics (Graduate Studies)	t	f	f		
EPIB 613	Introduction to Statistical Software.	Introduction to statistical software and data management; including basics of entering, manipulating data and elementary statistical analysis, SAS software, with reference to other packages of potential interest to students (R, Stata, SPSS).	0.0	Epidemiology and Biostatistics (Graduate Studies)	t	f	f	Prerequisite: Enrolment in Epidemiology stream program or permission of instructor.	
EPIB 621	Data Analysis in Health Sciences.	Univariate and multivariate statistical techniques for continuous categorical and survival data. Topics include generalized linear models, multiple linear and logistic regression, introductory survival analysis, model selection. Maximum likelihood and Bayesean approaches will be presented.	0.0	Epidemiology and Biostatistics (Graduate Studies)	f	t	f		
