FMED 301	TCP Family Medicine.	In this three-week course, students will build upon their knowledge of Family Medicine through a series of structured learning activities, coupled with organized clinical sessions highlighting the importance of interdisciplinary care. The various elements of this course will prepare students for clerkship by furthering their understanding of primary care, patientcentered care, and the organization of the Quebec health care system.	0.0	Family Medicine (Faculty of Medicine & Hlth Sci)	f	t	t	\N	\N
