PHIL 441	Philosophy of Science 2.	An analysis of some key philosophical ideas in science and technology, e.g. problem, explanation, forecast, testability and truth.	0.0	Philosophy (Faculty of Arts)	f	f	f	Prerequisite: PHIL 341 or written permission of the instructor	\N
